      </div>

      <div class="situation-card reveal d7">
        <button class="situation-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="situation-label">"I grieved fully and I'm ready to move forward."</span>
          <span class="situation-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" /></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="situation-answer">
          <div class="situation-answer-inner">
            <div class="workflow">
              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Pillar</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Pillar IV — Death: Return to the Whole</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Tenet</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Tenet XI — Grieve Fully. Then Move.</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-body">This is the whole arc of the tenet lived out. You did not rush past the grief, and you are not letting it become permanent. Moving forward is not a betrayal of what you lost — it is the proper continuation of a life that honored it.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Voices</div>
                <p class="workflow-quote">"Make the best use of what is in your power, and take the rest as it happens."</p>
                <div class="workflow-cite">— Epictetus, Enchiridion, Chapter 1</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">Your Practice</div>
                <p class="workflow-action">Write one sentence marking this moment: what you lost, what you honored in the grief, and where you are turning your energy now. Keep it. It is a record of your capacity. Then take one concrete forward-facing action today — something you deferred while grieving — and begin it.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-links">
